Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: another googly! Umar reads it, though perhaps a little late, and gets the bat down just in time to keep it out
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: Umar stays deep in the crease, working the ball into the leg side. He finds space there, and they're hustle back for a second
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Umar Akmal, 2 runs

Commentary: this will help! Tossed up by Yasir, but Ahsan just clears his left leg and slogs it over long on
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Ahsan Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: slightly short, and it's cut out to the cover sweeper
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Ahsan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: tapped back to the bowler, who collects it and fakes a shy back at the stumps. Umar is unmoved
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: almost done in the flight! He floated this one up outside off, and Umar was a little too early into his drive, the ball taking the inside edge and rolling to fine leg
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Umar Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: big spin and he's beaten on the outside edge
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Ahsan Ali, no run

Commentary: too short from Yasir, and the over is book-ended by boundaries as Ahsan pulls this one away to midwicket
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Ahsan Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: 144km/h loosener from Rauf, and Umar has a go at it outside off, getting a thick edge down to third man
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Umar Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: this one seams in off the track, Umar waiting in the crease and tucking to leg for one
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Umar Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: rising delivery outside off at 142km/h, but Ahsan deals with it well, guiding a single to third man
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Ahsan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: beaten outside off by one that bounces a little more than he was expecting, beating the cut
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: got him! Umar offers catching practice to Gauhar behind the stumps. The short ball rushes him even as he tries to guide the ball down, and a thin edge is through to the keeper as Rauf sets off on a celebratory run
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Umar Akmal, OUT
Dismissal_text: Umar Akmal c †Gauhar Ali b Haris Rauf 9 (13b 1x4 0x6) SR: 69.23

Commentary: He's got him first ball! Or has he? Rauf fires in a searing yorker at Sarfraz' toes, the ball tailing in and hitting him on the boot. The appeal is confident, and the finger goes up, but Sarfraz reviews it straight away. And it's a good one to review, as the curve in through the air was taking the ball down the leg side. But hang on, Anderson has also broken the stumps at the striker's end as the batsmen tried to take a single. Ahsan was short of his ground, but it can't be out as a decision had already been given on the lbw at the other end. Fakhar comes to talk to the umpire, as does Devcich, but the ball was dead so he couldn't have been run out
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: googly to start, and it's chopped into the covers
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Ahsan Ali, no run

Commentary: slog swept into the stands! Ahsan picked the length early and sent it arcing away right out of the middle
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Ahsan Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: another googly, and Ahsan taps to cover for a single
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Ahsan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: bottom edged into the ground, the keeper stops it with his pads
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: Sarfraz is off the mark, guiding a wrong 'un down to third man
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: tapped out through cover for one more
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: clipped to wide long on, and they're back for two
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: Sarfraz walks into a drive that goes straight to Anderson at cover, they take him on and the throw is wide
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: Ahsan is forward to drive to mid off, but he's hit it too well for a quick single this time
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Ahsan Ali, no run

Commentary: Rauf charges in and delivers a full one at 147km/h, Ahsan getting his bat down just in time to find a single to the leg side
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Ahsan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good-looking drive from Sarfraz, but he can't quite thread it through the cover field, Fakhar diving in the field to keep them to one
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: slips down the leg side
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Ahsan Ali, 1 wide

Commentary: an easy single to end the over
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Ahsan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: short, Ahsan pulls but he can't get it away
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Ahsan Ali, no run

Commentary: Ahsan walks across into a length delivery angled in to him from around the stumps, tucking a brace behind square
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Ahsan Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: angled down on the off side, where the fielder at short third stops it and throws at the stumps with Sarfraz not even in the frame, but he misses and they take another on the overthrow. Anderson was the fielder
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Ahsan Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: Rahat comes back over the wicket and Ahsan is half forward to press through mid off
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Ahsan Ali, 1 run
Rahat Ali to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: another easy single. There was a call for two, but the fielder was in too quickly off the boundary at midwicket, keeping them to one
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Ahsan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: bowled him! Googly from Lamichhane. I'm not convinced Ahsan read it. He was deep in his crease and waiting to pull the ball into the leg side, but it rushed in to him - turning appreciably - to rattle the stumps
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Ahsan Ali, OUT

Commentary: almost! Another wrong 'un from Smith, but the bat comes down at the last moment to keep it out
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Smith, 1 run

Commentary: nudged into the leg side, Sarfraz wants two but there's only one to be had
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: flighted, and it's pushed into the off side
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Smith, no run

Commentary: a play and a miss, and Gauhar fumbles his take. Sarfraz calls for a non-existent single, and Smith would have been out by a distance had the throw hit the stumps
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Smith, 1 run

Commentary: swept out to long leg for a single
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: this was always on the cards! The running had been all over the place. Sarfraz drives to cover - straight at Fakhar Zaman. Smith, a little inexplicably, sets off for a single that never was. Sarfraz never moved from the crease, and if there was a call he didn't respond. As the throw comes in, Smith doesn't even bother trying to make his ground as he's so far out
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, OUT
Dismissal_text: DR Smith run out (Fakhar Zaman) 2 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

Commentary: Sarfraz sets himself for a pull over the leg side field, but he mistimes the shot and it's just a single
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: Wiese comes round the stumps, looking for a yorker, but fires it down the leg side
Commentary_short: Wiese to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 wide

Commentary: nudged off the hip, and down to fine leg for one
Commentary_short: Wiese to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: tip-and-run single into the leg side from Sarfraz
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball from Wiese, Nawaz taps it to cover and there's another manic run. The fielder hurls in a shy, but it goes wide. Direct hit would have had Nawaz. Yasir was the fielder
Commentary_short: Wiese to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: pulled powerfully, and well in front of square. Wiese digs this one in, but it just sits up to be hit
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: could have been another run out! Another risky run after tapping the ball to cover, but the fielders in the circle are not in tight, so the temptation is on to test them. Again, a direct hit might have had him
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: big appeal for lbw as Sarfraz comes forward and is hit on the pad, but it looked like it was headed down the leg side
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 leg bye

Commentary: and another! Tapped straight to backward point, and they take the fielder on. A better throw, and Sarfraz would have been well short
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: Sarfraz backs away, collecting a single with a backfoot punch
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: this time they hit the stumps, but it only brings overthrows! Nawaz nudges to point and they're off again, but they've run this one quickly and he was well in
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Mohammad Nawaz, 2 runs

Commentary: play and a miss outside off, Nawaz beaten on the cut
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: Sarfraz comes down the track, slicing his drive up and over cover. It doesn't have the legs to reach the cover sweeper, but they're back for two
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: worked into vacant space on the leg side, and an ambled single is the result
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: launched up into the night sky, and it's got the power behind it to clear the rope. That also brings up the team 100
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Mohammad Nawaz, SIX runs

Commentary: tapped down to point, where Anderson sprints in but can't stop the quick single
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: Sarfraz steps back to pull, rolling his wrists on the shot and getting the ball out to the man at deep square
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: Nawaz is up on one leg to flick a pull down to fine leg, but he finds the fielder
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: Rauf hits a good length outside off, Nawaz driving to cover
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: full and straight at 142km/h, and Nawaz swings it out to deep square
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: Sarfraz waits, deep in his crease, to force the ball out to deep cover. Nelson comes up
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: big appeal from Rauf, but it's headed down the leg side ... Well, they ask for a review but it's a total waste as the ball was clearly headed down leg
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: Sarfraz backs away and drives straight, Devcich at long on sprinting across and putting in a dive at the boundary to keep them to two
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: short ball from Rauf, and Sarfraz can't lay bat on his pull shot
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: beaten in the flight! Lamichhane put some real flight on this one and beat Nawaz' drive, but the keeper misses his take and they take a bye
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 bye

Commentary: Sarfraz slices to point, where the fielder is still on the edge of the ring so they steal a single
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: another wonderful piece of bowling, floated right up on the breeze, and Nawaz doesn't pick the wrong 'un either, sweeping right across it and hitting nothing
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: legbreak, and it's played with the turn into the leg side
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: Sarfraz waits in the crease, swiping the ball down to long on for one
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: excellent finish, Lamichhane beating Nawaz yet again with a googly that rushed right past the outside edge of his flailing bat
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: slammed through extra cover! Change of pace from Wiese, and Sarfraz spots it early, clearing his left leg and smashing his drive through the gap
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: full toss from Wiese, and Sarfraz swats it out to long leg - but there's protection on the boundary
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide, and Nawaz brings his bat down on it to collect a single to cover
Commentary_short: Wiese to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: pulled over fine leg! Another change-up from Wiese, the slow offcutter bouncer, but Sarfraz won't be hoodwinked, waiting on it and deliberately pulling it in the air down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: pinpoint yorker, another tight run, and another missed run out! Sarfraz gets bat on it and just sets off. The keeper runs in, picks up the ball and throws at the stumps, but misses. Nawaz was out if he had hit
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: through the finger tips! Nawaz throws his hands at a wide one, slapping it just over a leaping fielder at extra cover
Commentary_short: Wiese to Mohammad Nawaz, 2 runs

Commentary: good start from Rauf, who can bowl at fiery pace but starts with a canny slower ball at 114km/h, deceiving Sarfraz who drives and misses outside off
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, no run

Commentary: smeared through midwicket! Sarfraz clears his leg, picks the length, and smacks it right between the two fielders on the boundary
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: length again, Sarfraz targets wide long on but the fielder runs around and stops the shot, on the bounce
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: caught at the boundary! Rauf sends down an offcutter, on a length, and he goes for a big pull. He hit it fairly well, but not well enough to get it over Sohail Akhtar, who is very close to the boundary when he takes the catch. So close, in fact, that the umpire's want to have another look at where his foot was in relation to the boundary marker. Seems it's a clean catch though. Is there a twist?
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Mohammad Nawaz, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Nawaz c Sohail Akhtar b Haris Rauf 19 (18b 0x4 1x6) SR: 105.55

Commentary: yorker from Rauf, tailing in at 144km/h, but Sarfraz gets the bat down on it to find a single to third man
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: rising delivery on off stump, Anwar Ali rides the bounce and taps to point, and they take the single
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Anwar Ali, 1 run

Commentary: bowled him! Wiese runs in and bowls an inswinging yorker, right on his toes. The ball reverses in and dips, zipping under Anwar's bat and shattering the stumps
Commentary_short: Wiese to Anwar Ali, OUT

Commentary: another very full ball from Wiese, and Tanvir jams his drive out through cover to turn the strike over
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sohail Tanvir, 1 run

Commentary: big swing from Sarfraz to a full ball, the ball coming off the cue end and rolling slowly down to long on - so slowly that there's time for them to rush back for a second
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 2 runs

Commentary: full again, driven down the ground and this time it's just a single as Devcich is quickly in
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run

Commentary: and he turns the strike back over with a single, clubbing a length ball out to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sohail Tanvir, 1 run

Commentary: Sarfraz wins it! A low full toss from Wiese, Sarfraz bends low and belts it over wide long on. The fielder out there thought he was in business, but the ball just kept going.
Commentary_short: Wiese to Sarfaraz Ahmed, SIX runs
